HEADWORD: eye-opening
<hw>eye-opening</hw> <pos>a.</pos> <def>Causing one suddenly to learn or
understand what was not previously known; <as>as, an
<ex>eye-opening</ex> look into the private machinations of the
governor</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

